<HEADLINE> Jeb Bush Kicks Off Brazilian Visit  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAO PAULO, Brazil (AP) -- Florida Gov. Jeb Bush kicked off a
three-day visit here in the company of 200 executives hoping to
foster greater business opportunities between their state and South
America's largest country.
</P>
<P>
   ''These missions give a chance for a lot of businesses -- many of
whom are small businesses -- to get acquainted. And if you come in
the scale we've come in, the results are likely to be impressive,''
