   Bush started Monday with a luncheon sponsored by Cutrale Citrus
Juices USA, the affiliate of a Brazilian firm building orange
groves on 15,000 acres in Florida. Brazilian citrus growers have
long complained about U.S. tariffs on their oranges and orange
juice.
</P>
<P>
   Bush also was scheduled to address the American Chamber of
Commerce in Sao Paulo and meet with President Fernando Henrique
Cardoso in Brasilia before heading home Wednesday.
</P>
