<HEADLINE> Dow, Nasdaq Each Slip 42  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is down 42
points in today's early going. Losing issues on the New York Stock
Exchange hold a five-to-four lead over gainers.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index is off 42 points and the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 Stock Index is down four points.
</P>
<P>
   There should be no lack of information for Wall Street to
consider today.
</P>
<P>
   Nonetheless, we still may not see much trading activity.
</P>
<P>
   Even though there are some big profit reports already released,
and some key inflation data, investors could be standing by for
some more figures.
</P>
