<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India To Upgrade Aircraft Fleet  </HEADLINE>
By INDRANIL SINGH
<TEXT>
<P>
   PATNA, India (AP) -- India on Tuesday promised to work more
swiftly to modernize its aircraft fleet in the wake of the crash of
an aging Boeing 737-200 that killed 56 people.
</P>
<P>
   ''New aircraft will be bought,'' Civil Aviation Minister Sharad
Yadav said a day after the state-owned Alliance Air plane crashed
into a housing complex. ''The Alliance Air planes are old and we
have asked the government to speed up the bidding process.''
</P>
<P>
   The jet that crashed was 20 years old and was part of a fleet
that was to be phased out in two years. It was last checked
thoroughly March 19, in accordance with regulations concerning
older aircraft, authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   In a statement, officials of the airline said the plane was
airworthy and denied allegations the company had been lax on
safety.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile Tuesday, experts investigated whether a sudden burst
of wind may have pushed down the jetliner.
</P>
<P>
   P.N. Bopanna, an engineer who survived the crash, told reporters
hours after he was rescued that that plane lurched and wobbled
before it went down.
</P>
<P>
   When wind shear occurs, a sudden gust of air initially pushes
the aircraft forward. The air current then pushes the plane toward
the ground. The phenomenon occurs especially during takeoffs and
landings.
</P>
<P>
   Civil Aviation Ministry secretary A.H. Jung told reporters
Monday that the pilot may have been flying too low as he made his
second approach to Patna. ''He had lost height or partially
misjudged it, according to our regulations,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   A judge will head a team of experts to investigate the crash.
Engineers have recovered the ''black boxes,'' the sealed units that
record flight data and the conversation in the cockpit.
</P>
<P>
   Also Tuesday, the body of the 56th victim of the crash was
recovered, said S.P. Modi, director of the airport authority of
Patna. It was apparently the remains of one of five people killed
in the housing complex, where several people were also injured.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
