<HEADLINE> Atlantic City casino workers wins $1 million on Internet giveaway  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ATLANTIC CITY, N.J. (AP) - John Grasso is no stranger to instant
riches. As a slot machine supervisor at Harrah's Atlantic City, he
gets to deliver them all the time.
</P>
<P>
   But now, the 43-year-old Hammonton man is in the money himself.
</P>
<P>
   Grasso won $1 million from iWon.com, an Internet portal that
gives away $10,000 daily, $1 million once a month and $10 million
once a year to users.
</P>
<P>
   ''Usually, I pay out jackpots. It's nice to be on the other
side,'' said Grasso, a 20-year employee of the casino.
</P>
<P>
   He said he plans to keep working, but will use the money - about
$40,000 a year for 20 years, before taxes - to finance his sons'
education, pay off his debts and take a nice vacation.
</P>
<P>
   ''Through the years, I have watched so many people win enormous
amounts of money. But I'm always the one who gives the money away.
And now it's me, the winner. I'm still in shock,'' Grasso said.
</P>
<P>
   His victory was announced Monday night during a television
commercial for iWon.com.
</P>
</TEXT>
