<DOCNO> APW20000718.0143 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-18 19:38 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Phillies Send Down Coggin, Shrenk  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The Philadelphia Phillies sent right-hander
David Coggin to Triple-A Scranton/Wilkes-Barre on Tuesday one day
after he beat the New York Yankees.
</P>
<P>
   Coggin allowed three earned runs in five innings for his second
major league win as Philadelphia won 10-8. He was 2-0 with a 5.33
ERA in five starts. Right-hander Steve Schrenk was also demoted.
</P>
<P>
   The Phillies recalled catcher Gary Bennett from Scranton and
activated left-hander Mark Holzemer from the disabled list.
</P>
<P>
   Bennett, who was hitting .335 with nine homers and 40 RBIs at
Scranton, was needed as insurance after starting catcher Mike
Lieberthal sprained his left ankle Monday. Lieberthal is expected
to miss 3-4 games.
</P>
<P>
   Holzemer, out with a strained left hamstring, was activated
after making three rehab starts at Double-A Reading. He had a 2.38
ERA in 11 1-3 innings with the Phillies before getting hurt.
</P>
<P>
   Schrenk went 2-3 with a 7.33 ERA with the Phillies.
</P>
</TEXT>
