Yankees Beat Phillies 3-1
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Denny Neagle made quite a first impression at a most
opportune time for the New York Yankees. Neagle took a shutout into the eighth
inning as the Yankees beat the Philadelphia Phillies 3-1 tonight. David Justice
hit a solo homer and Bernie Williams added a two-run triple off Curt Schilling
(5-6) for New York. Schilling finished with a four-hitter. The left-hander, who
was 8-2 for the Reds, allowed one run and five hits in eight innings. He struck
out three and walked two.
</P>
