<HEADLINE> Police arrest Staten Island man in connection to fatal police crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP) - Police have charged a Staten Island man on
Tuesday in connection with the death of a Staten Island police
officer who was killed when he crashed his unmarked car into a
utility pole while chasing a motorcycle with stolen plates.
</P>
<P>
   Guido Tritto, 43, was charged with manslaughter and other counts
including reckless endangerment and leaving the scene of an
accident. He was arrested Tuesday morning at his home by officers
acting on a phone tip, police said. He has an arrest record dating
back to 1974.
</P>
<P>
   Officer John Kelly, 31, died Monday, the second officer to die
in the line of duty this year.
</P>
<P>
   Kelly, who was in uniform and working alone, was apparently
chasing the motorcycle when he crashed. His 1999 Chevy Lumina was
heavily impacted on the driver's side.
</P>
<P>
   Viewings have been scheduled for Wednesday and Thursday, and
Kelly's funeral is on Friday.
</P>
</TEXT>
