<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philadelphia Workers Set Strike Day  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Thousands of city workers are threatening to
go on strike July 25 -- a week before the Republican National
Convention -- if their union and the city do not agree on a contract
by then.
</P>
<P>
   If a strike happens and it continues beyond the start of the
Republican National Convention on July 31, that could mean piles of
uncollected garbage all over the city just as thousands of people
come to town.
</P>
<P>
   Herman ''Pete'' Matthews, president of the blue-collar District
Council 33 of the American Federation of State, County and
Municipal Employees, said after a meeting Tuesday night that he has
seen little progress in three weeks of negotiations.
</P>
<P>
   He said he hopes that setting a strike deadline will put
pressure on city negotiators.
</P>
<P>
   About 14,000 AFSCME members are eligible to strike. Police
officers and firefighters are forbidden by law from striking.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-07-18-00 2336 </TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW20000718.0219 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-18 23:36 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Police chase man from New Jersey to New York before apprehending him </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP) - A 20-year-old man who led police on a car chase
from New Jersey into New York and then tried to carjack an off-duty
police officer was apprehended on the Cross Bronx Expressway, a
Port Authority spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
   Adrian Burnett stole a black BMW from a car dealership in
Tenafly, N.J., and led several officers on a chase across the lower
level of the George Washington Bridge onto the expressway around 7
p.m. Tuesday, Port Authority spokesman Bill Cahill said.
</P>
<P>
   After encountering traffic, Burnett jumped out of the car, ran
along the expressway and climbed into a black jeep driven by an
off-duty New York police officer, Cahill said. He then exited the
jeep and continued running.
</P>
<P>
   New York and Port Authority police officers used their cruisers
to box in Burnett, who tried to climb a wall before the officers
grabbed him, Cahill said.
</P>
<P>
   Burnett was charged in New York with multiple crimes, including
grand larceny and resisting arrest. New Jersey charges were
pending.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
